    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        SHEET METAL REPAIRS - PREPARE PANEL AREA FOR PANEL REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
        <title>PREPARE PANEL AREA FOR PANEL REMOVAL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove grille sections. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s16006_55.xml" xrefid="hl1600623">CAB GRILLE ASSEMBLY
                    <xref refid="hl1600623"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove fender skirt. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s16006_38.xml" xrefid="hl1600617">CAB FILLER PANELS
                    <xref refid="hl1600617"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove right turn signal light if applicable. To remove turn light, remove screws securing
                light assembly to cab and disconnect wire.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove windshield glass and seal (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600659">Figure 59</hotlnk>). Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s16006_19.xml" xrefid="hl1600609">WINDSHIELD GLASS
                    <xref refid="hl1600609"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600659" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600659" filename="../figg16/G1600659.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Removing Windshield Glass From Cab</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove mounting screws and detach air vent cover. Also, detach duct from back side of
                panel.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mark door hinge mounting position and remove door and hinge from hinge pillar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600660">Figure 60</hotlnk>). Note the number and location of adjusting shims. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s16006_23.xml" xrefid="hl1600611">.REMOVE DOOR
                    <xref refid="hl1600611"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600660" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600660" filename="../figg16/G1600660.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 60. Removing Door Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
